<doc>
  <member name="AMOVERLAYFX">
    <summary>
      <para>Specifies effects on a DirectDraw hardware overlay surface.</para>
    </summary>
    <seealso href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/DirectShow/directshow-enumerated-types">DirectShow Enumerated Types</seealso>
    <seealso cref="IAMOverlayFX Interface" />
  </member>
  <member name="AMOVERLAYFX.AMOVERFX_NOFX">
    <summary>
      <para>Normal video (no effects).</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="AMOVERLAYFX.AMOVERFX_MIRRORLEFTRIGHT">
    <summary>
      <para>Mirror the overlay across the vertical axis.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="AMOVERLAYFX.AMOVERFX_MIRRORUPDOWN">
    <summary>
      <para>Mirror the overlay across the horizontal axis.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="AMOVERLAYFX.AMOVERFX_DEINTERLACE">
    <summary>
      <para>When used in <see cref="IAMOverlayFX.QueryOverlayFXCaps" />, this flag specifies whether the hardware can support the DirectDraw 7 DDOVERFX_DEINTERLACE hint. When used with the <see cref="IAMOverlayFX.GetOverlayFX" /> or <see cref="IAMOverlayFX.SetOverlayFX" /> methods, this flag indicates that the overlay should be deinterlaced if possible.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
</doc>